    "Within the slow-roll consistency relation, the GWB spectral slope is therefore slightly red-tilted, causing this signal to be out of reach of most current and planned GW detectors such as PTAs, LISA, aLIGO, aVirgo or the Einstein Telescope.",
    "On the other hand, it is fair to consider that the spectral slope could vary over the large frequency span ranging from CMB scales to those probed by GW detectors (Lasky et al. 2016).",
